massachusetts general hospital as project manager on international projects specifically she was responsible for coordinating efforts on the application of the cost effectiveness of preventing aids complications cepac model to identify cost effective strategies of care in india south africa and cote d ivoire she received her masters in public health from the harvard school of public health 2003 and her areas of interest include health economics disease modeling and international health events & presentations stanford health policy panel on evaluating healthcare quality and outcomes july 27 2009 seminar series nomita divi jeremy goldhaber fiebert grant miller search chp search within everything courses events fellowships news op eds people publications research other pages support map & directions contact rss+ rss xml feeds freeman spogli institute for international studies encina hall 616 serra st stanford ca 94305 6055 tel 650 736 0815 fax 650 725 2592 mail code 6055
